One hundred and sixteen Nigerian nationals brought back from Tripoli, Libya, yesterday by the International Organization on Migration in an effort facilitated by the Nigerian Embassy in Tripoli. Among those repatriated were illegal migrants and those trafficked. This was disclosed in a statement by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs. The statement said they were expected to arrive the Murtala Mohammed International Airport Lagos, on-board a Buraq Air flight at 9:40pm Nigerian time. The returnees were expected to be received on arrival by officials of relevant governmentÂ  agencies. Repatriation: Again, 116 Nigerians arrive from Libya 330 Nigerians return from Libya Many Nigerians among victims of Libyan airstrike